{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"Economists have been exploring\npeople's behavior for hundreds of years:"},{"time":6880,"text":"how we make decisions,"},{"time":8480,"text":"how we act individually and in groups,"},{"time":11560,"text":"how we exchange value."},{"time":14760,"text":"They've studied the institutions\nthat facilitate our trade,"},{"time":18240,"text":"like legal systems,"},{"time":19680,"text":"corporations,"},{"time":21520,"text":"marketplaces."},{"time":23600,"text":"But there is a new,\ntechnological institution"},{"time":27080,"text":"that will fundamentally change\nhow we exchange value,"},{"time":31120,"text":"and it's called the blockchain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34040,"text":"Now, that's a pretty bold statement,"},{"time":36720,"text":"but if you take nothing else\naway from this talk,"},{"time":39880,"text":"I actually want you to remember"},{"time":41640,"text":"that while blockchain technology\nis relatively new,"},{"time":45600,"text":"it's also a continuation\nof a very human story,"},{"time":50000,"text":"and the story is this."},{"time":52080,"text":"As humans, we find ways"},{"time":54120,"text":"to lower uncertainty about one another"},{"time":56960,"text":"so that we can exchange value."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61080,"text":"Now, one of the first people\nto really explore the idea"},{"time":64599,"text":"of institutions as a tool in economics"},{"time":67800,"text":"to lower our uncertainties\nabout one another"},{"time":70280,"text":"and be able to do trade"},{"time":72200,"text":"was the Nobel economist Douglass North."},{"time":75680,"text":"He passed away at the end of 2015,"},{"time":77840,"text":"but North pioneered what's called\n\"new institutional economics.\""},{"time":83120,"text":"And what he meant by institutions\nwere really just formal rules"},{"time":87320,"text":"like a constitution,"},{"time":89320,"text":"and informal constraints, like bribery."},{"time":93280,"text":"These institutions are really the grease"},{"time":96200,"text":"that allow our economic\nwheels to function,"},{"time":99160,"text":"and we can see this play out\nover the course of human history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":103120,"text":"If we think back to when we were\nhunter-gatherer economies,"},{"time":106600,"text":"we really just traded\nwithin our village structure."},{"time":109560,"text":"We had some informal constraints in place,"},{"time":112000,"text":"but we enforced\nall of our trade with violence"},{"time":115560,"text":"or social repercussions."},{"time":117960,"text":"As our societies grew more complex"},{"time":120320,"text":"and our trade routes grew more distant,"},{"time":123560,"text":"we built up more formal institutions,"},{"time":126600,"text":"institutions like banks for currency,"},{"time":129960,"text":"governments, corporations."},{"time":132680,"text":"These institutions\nhelped us manage our trade"},{"time":135240,"text":"as the uncertainty\nand the complexity grew,"},{"time":138280,"text":"and our personal control was much lower."},{"time":141560,"text":"Eventually with the internet,\nwe put these same institutions online."},{"time":146600,"text":"We built platform marketplaces\nlike Amazon, eBay, Alibaba,"},{"time":151000,"text":"just faster institutions\nthat act as middlemen"},{"time":154560,"text":"to facilitate human economic activity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":159840,"text":"As Douglass North saw it,"},{"time":162000,"text":"institutions are a tool\nto lower uncertainty"},{"time":165680,"text":"so that we can connect and exchange\nall kinds of value in society."},{"time":170840,"text":"And I believe we are now entering"},{"time":173200,"text":"a further and radical evolution"},{"time":176200,"text":"of how we interact and trade,"},{"time":178680,"text":"because for the first time,\nwe can lower uncertainty"},{"time":182280,"text":"not just with political\nand economic institutions,"},{"time":185880,"text":"like our banks, our corporations,\nour governments,"},{"time":189640,"text":"but we can do it with technology alone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193920,"text":"So what is the blockchain?"},{"time":195960,"text":"Blockchain technology\nis a decentralized database"},{"time":200040,"text":"that stores a registry\nof assets and transactions"},{"time":203600,"text":"across a peer-to-peer network."},{"time":206160,"text":"It's basically a public registry"},{"time":208320,"text":"of who owns what and who transacts what."},{"time":211920,"text":"The transactions are secured\nthrough cryptography,"},{"time":214920,"text":"and over time, that transaction history\ngets locked in blocks of data"},{"time":220720,"text":"that are then cryptographically\nlinked together and secured."},{"time":225360,"text":"This creates an immutable,\nunforgeable record"},{"time":229560,"text":"of all of the transactions\nacross this network."},{"time":233400,"text":"This record is replicated\non every computer that uses the network."}]},{"cues":[{"time":239240,"text":"It's not an app."},{"time":241080,"text":"It's not a company."},{"time":243120,"text":"I think it's closest in description\nto something like Wikipedia."},{"time":247800,"text":"We can see everything on Wikipedia."},{"time":249880,"text":"It's a composite view that's constantly\nchanging and being updated."},{"time":255880,"text":"We can also track those changes\nover time on Wikipedia,"},{"time":259560,"text":"and we can create our own wikis,"},{"time":261880,"text":"because at their core,\nthey're just a data infrastructure."},{"time":266600,"text":"On Wikipedia, it's an open platform\nthat stores words and images"},{"time":272120,"text":"and the changes to that data over time."},{"time":275520,"text":"On the blockchain,"},{"time":277000,"text":"you can think of it\nas an open infrastructure"},{"time":279960,"text":"that stores many kinds of assets."},{"time":283760,"text":"It stores the history of custodianship,"},{"time":286520,"text":"ownership and location"},{"time":288760,"text":"for assets like\nthe digital currency Bitcoin,"},{"time":292440,"text":"other digital assets"},{"time":294040,"text":"like a title of ownership of IP."},{"time":298480,"text":"It could be a certificate, a contract,"},{"time":301640,"text":"real world objects,"},{"time":302920,"text":"even personal identifiable information."},{"time":307080,"text":"There are of course other\ntechnical details to the blockchain,"},{"time":310960,"text":"but at its core, that's how it works."},{"time":313000,"text":"It's this public registry\nthat stores transactions in a network"},{"time":317360,"text":"and is replicated so that it's very secure\nand hard to tamper with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":323120,"text":"Which brings me to my point"},{"time":325280,"text":"of how blockchains lower uncertainty"},{"time":328360,"text":"and how they therefore promise\nto transform our economic systems"},{"time":332520,"text":"in radical ways."},{"time":335880,"text":"So uncertainty is kind of a big term"},{"time":338240,"text":"in economics,"},{"time":339640,"text":"but I want to go through three forms of it"},{"time":341720,"text":"that we face in almost all\nof our everyday transactions,"},{"time":345120,"text":"where blockchains can play a role."},{"time":347240,"text":"We face uncertainties\nlike not knowing who we're dealing with,"},{"time":350640,"text":"not having visibility into a transaction"},{"time":353480,"text":"and not having recourse\nif things go wrong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":357520,"text":"So let's take the first example,\nnot knowing who we're dealing with."},{"time":361720,"text":"Say I want to buy\na used smartphone on eBay."},{"time":365760,"text":"The first thing I'm going to do\nis look up who I'm buying from."},{"time":369600,"text":"Are they a power user?"},{"time":371360,"text":"Do they have great reviews and ratings,\nor do they have no profile at all?"},{"time":376960,"text":"Reviews, ratings, checkmarks:"},{"time":379760,"text":"these are the attestations\nabout our identities"},{"time":383400,"text":"that we cobble together today"},{"time":385040,"text":"and use to lower uncertainty\nabout who we're dealing with."},{"time":389840,"text":"But the problem is\nthey're very fragmented."},{"time":392880,"text":"Think about how many profiles you have."},{"time":396520,"text":"Blockchains allow for us\nto create an open, global platform"},{"time":402040,"text":"on which to store any attestation\nabout any individual"},{"time":406440,"text":"from any source."},{"time":408480,"text":"This allows us to create a user-controlled"},{"time":411800,"text":"portable identity."},{"time":415800,"text":"More than a profile,"},{"time":417720,"text":"it means you can selectively reveal"},{"time":421040,"text":"the different attributes about you"},{"time":423000,"text":"that help facilitate trade or interaction,"},{"time":426320,"text":"for instance that a government\nissued you an ID,"},{"time":429200,"text":"or that you're over 21,"},{"time":431480,"text":"by revealing the cryptographic proof"},{"time":434120,"text":"that these details exist\nand are signed off on."},{"time":438960,"text":"Having this kind of portable identity"},{"time":441040,"text":"around the physical world\nand the digital world"},{"time":444080,"text":"means we can do all kinds of human trade"},{"time":447400,"text":"in a totally new way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":450600,"text":"So I've talked about how blockchains\ncould lower uncertainty"},{"time":453520,"text":"in who we're dealing with."},{"time":455080,"text":"The second uncertainty that we often face"},{"time":457680,"text":"is just not having transparency\ninto our interactions."},{"time":461600,"text":"Say you're going to send me\nthat smartphone by mail."},{"time":464360,"text":"I want some degree of transparency."},{"time":466080,"text":"I want to know that the product I bought\nis the same one that arrives in the mail"},{"time":470400,"text":"and that there's some record\nfor how it got to me."},{"time":472800,"text":"This is true not just\nfor electronics like smartphones,"},{"time":475440,"text":"but for many kinds of goods and data,"},{"time":478640,"text":"things like medicine, luxury goods,"},{"time":482000,"text":"any kind of data or product\nthat we don't want tampered with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":486880,"text":"The problem in many companies,"},{"time":489120,"text":"especially those that produce\nsomething complicated like a smartphone,"},{"time":492480,"text":"is they're managing\nall of these different vendors"},{"time":495000,"text":"across a horizontal supply chain."},{"time":498240,"text":"All of these people\nthat go into making a product,"},{"time":500840,"text":"they don't have the same database."},{"time":502520,"text":"They don't use the same infrastructure,"},{"time":504560,"text":"and so it becomes really hard to see\ntransparently a product evolve over time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511840,"text":"Using the blockchain, we can create"},{"time":513799,"text":"a shared reality\nacross nontrusting entities."},{"time":518640,"text":"By this I mean"},{"time":519880,"text":"all of these nodes in the network\ndo not need to know each other"},{"time":523280,"text":"or trust each other,"},{"time":524720,"text":"because they each have the ability"},{"time":526880,"text":"to monitor and validate\nthe chain for themselves."},{"time":531040,"text":"Think back to Wikipedia."},{"time":532800,"text":"It's a shared database,"},{"time":535000,"text":"and even though it has multiple readers"},{"time":537840,"text":"and multiple writers at the same time,"},{"time":539960,"text":"it has one single truth."},{"time":542720,"text":"So we can create that using blockchains."},{"time":544840,"text":"We can create a decentralized database\nthat has the same efficiency of a monopoly"},{"time":550840,"text":"without actually creating\nthat central authority."},{"time":554200,"text":"So all of these vendors,\nall sorts of companies,"},{"time":556640,"text":"can interact using the same database\nwithout trusting one another."},{"time":562200,"text":"It means for consumers,\nwe can have a lot more transparency."},{"time":565760,"text":"As a real-world object travels along,"},{"time":567920,"text":"we can see its digital certificate\nor token move on the blockchain,"},{"time":573120,"text":"adding value as it goes."},{"time":576360,"text":"This is a whole new world\nin terms of our visibility."}]},{"cues":[{"time":581720,"text":"So I've talked about how blockchains\ncan lower our uncertainties about identity"},{"time":587240,"text":"and how they change\nwhat we mean about transparency"},{"time":590480,"text":"in long distances and complex trades,\nlike in a supply chain."},{"time":595520,"text":"The last uncertainty that we often face"},{"time":597640,"text":"is one of the most open-ended,\nand it's reneging."},{"time":600920,"text":"What if you don't send me the smartphone?"},{"time":603440,"text":"Can I get my money back?"},{"time":605800,"text":"Blockchains allow us to write code,"},{"time":609520,"text":"binding contracts,"},{"time":611240,"text":"between individuals"},{"time":612920,"text":"and then guarantee\nthat those contracts will bear out"},{"time":616600,"text":"without a third party enforcer."},{"time":619720,"text":"So if we look at the smartphone example,\nyou could think about escrow."},{"time":623640,"text":"You are financing that phone,"},{"time":625760,"text":"but you don't need to release the funds"},{"time":628320,"text":"until you can verify\nthat all the conditions have been met."},{"time":631160,"text":"You got the phone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":634240,"text":"I think this is one\nof the most exciting ways"},{"time":636680,"text":"that blockchains lower our uncertainties,"},{"time":639840,"text":"because it means to some degree"},{"time":641440,"text":"we can collapse institutions\nand their enforcement."},{"time":647720,"text":"It means a lot of human economic activity"},{"time":650440,"text":"can get collateralized and automated,"},{"time":655480,"text":"and push a lot of human\nintervention to the edges,"},{"time":658560,"text":"the places where information moves\nfrom the real world to the blockchain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664880,"text":"I think what would probably\nfloor Douglass North"},{"time":667360,"text":"about this use of technology"},{"time":669760,"text":"is the fact that the very thing\nthat makes it work,"},{"time":672800,"text":"the very thing that keeps the blockchain\nsecure and verified,"},{"time":677360,"text":"is our mutual distrust."},{"time":681600,"text":"So rather than all of our uncertainties"},{"time":684720,"text":"slowing us down"},{"time":686360,"text":"and requiring institutions"},{"time":688880,"text":"like banks, our governments,\nour corporations,"},{"time":693360,"text":"we can actually harness\nall of that collective uncertainty"},{"time":697760,"text":"and use it to collaborate and exchange\nmore and faster and more open."}]},{"cues":[{"time":704800,"text":"Now, I don't want you\nto get the impression"},{"time":706880,"text":"that the blockchain\nis the solution to everything,"},{"time":709280,"text":"even though the media has said\nthat it's going to end world poverty,"},{"time":715840,"text":"it's also going to solve\nthe counterfeit drug problem"},{"time":718600,"text":"and potentially save the rainforest."},{"time":722320,"text":"The truth is, this technology\nis in its infancy,"},{"time":726320,"text":"and we're going to need to see\na lot of experiments take place"},{"time":729560,"text":"and probably fail"},{"time":731000,"text":"before we truly understand\nall of the use cases"},{"time":734560,"text":"for our economy."},{"time":737240,"text":"But there are tons of people\nworking on this,"},{"time":739440,"text":"from financial institutions"},{"time":741160,"text":"to technology companies,\nstart-ups and universities."},{"time":745120,"text":"And one of the reasons is\nthat it's not just an economic evolution."},{"time":750080,"text":"It's also an innovation\nin computer science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":757360,"text":"Blockchains give us\nthe technological capability"},{"time":760840,"text":"of creating a record of human exchange,"},{"time":764440,"text":"of exchange of currency,"},{"time":766720,"text":"of all kinds of digital\nand physical assets,"},{"time":770440,"text":"even of our own personal attributes,"},{"time":773040,"text":"in a totally new way."},{"time":775720,"text":"So in some ways,"},{"time":777080,"text":"they become a technological institution"},{"time":780080,"text":"that has a lot of the benefits"},{"time":781880,"text":"of the traditional institutions\nwe're used to using in society,"},{"time":786200,"text":"but it does this in a decentralized way."},{"time":790360,"text":"It does this by converting\na lot of our uncertainties"},{"time":793920,"text":"into certainties."}]},{"cues":[{"time":796360,"text":"So I think we need to start\npreparing ourselves,"},{"time":799920,"text":"because we are about to face a world"},{"time":802480,"text":"where distributed, autonomous institutions"},{"time":805640,"text":"have quite a significant role."}]},{"cues":[{"time":808600,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":809840,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":818400,"text":"Bruno Giussani: Thank you, Bettina."},{"time":820880,"text":"I think I understood that it's coming,"},{"time":824600,"text":"it offers a lot of potential,"},{"time":826520,"text":"and it's complex."},{"time":828720,"text":"What is your estimate\nfor the rate of adoption?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":835120,"text":"Bettina Warburg: I think\nthat's a really good question."},{"time":837760,"text":"My lab is pretty much focused"},{"time":839200,"text":"on going the enterprise\nand government route first,"},{"time":842680,"text":"because in reality,\nblockchain is a complex technology."},{"time":846240,"text":"How many of you actually understand\nhow the internet works?"},{"time":849040,"text":"But you use it every day,"},{"time":850720,"text":"so I think we're sort of facing\nthe same John Sculley idea"},{"time":854520,"text":"of technology should either be\ninvisible or beautiful,"},{"time":858200,"text":"and blockchain is kind of\nneither of those things right now,"},{"time":862080,"text":"so it's better suited\nfor either really early adopters"},{"time":866080,"text":"who kind of get it and can tinker around"},{"time":868320,"text":"or for finding those best use cases"},{"time":871320,"text":"like identity or asset tracking\nor smart contracts"},{"time":874520,"text":"that can be used at that level\nof an enterprise or government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":878560,"text":"BG: Thank you. Thanks for coming to TED."}]},{"cues":[{"time":880489,"text":"BW: Thanks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":881720,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}